function con= ff_to_mu% f'' [electrons/atom] to mu in [1/microns]% mu= (4piNe^2/mwc)*f'' (James, p. 138)%   = 2*rsubelectron*hc*Avogadro*rho*f''/ atomic_mass*energy%  Thus 4.208e3 = 2*rsube*hc*Av*10^-16[cm^2/AA^2]*10^-4[cm/micron]%       4.208e3 [AA/electron][ev-AA][atoms/mole][cm^2/AA^2][cm/micron]%       4.208e3 [ev-atoms-cm^3/electron-mole-micron]%   where rsube= 2.8179e-5 [A/electron]%           hc= 12398.4244 [eV-A]%       Av= 6.022e23 [atoms/mole]%       rho in [gms/cm^3]%       amu in [gms/mole]%       energy in [eV]%       fpp in [electrons/atom]% mu= (4208.031548* rho*( fpp+ ray+ comp))/( amu* energy) [1/microns]% Sean Brennan (bren@slac.stanford.edu)con= 4208.031548;